Classes in Js
  - class Surgeon{
  constructor(name,department){
    this.name=name;  // this is called property (this.name or whatever )
    this.department=department;

  }
}

// we use constructor to build an instance of the class 
// focus on the syntax of class very well 

--
// instance -> is an object created from the class that has the properties under constructor
// we called new to make that instance.

example ;


class Surgeon {
  constructor(name, department) {
    this.name = name;
    this.department = department;
  }
}
let surgeonRomero=new Surgeon('Francisco Romero','Cardiovascular');

let surgeonJackson=new Surgeon('Ruth Jackson','Orthopedics');

-- 
How to make getter methods or method inside class ;
ex;
In the Surgeon constructor, prepend the name and department properties with an underscore (_) to indicate they should not be accessed directly.
Checkpoint 2 Passed

